01:29:53.860 --> 01:30:10.300
Other than she said that when the star of Regulus, which is a blue star, when it appears red on the horizon at the dawn, uh, before the sun comes up and the gaze of the sphinx.

01:30:10.300 --> 01:30:13.620
In other words, I saw it in a vision, the whole thing.

01:30:13.760 --> 01:30:18.520
You can see the sphinx facing east and this thing's just cresting the top.

01:30:18.520 --> 01:30:26.080
But she said, when that happens, that will be a sign that ushers in a new knowledge for humanity.

01:30:27.820 --> 01:30:33.020
So does that mean the return of Jesus or the return of Christ consciousness?

01:30:33.020 --> 01:30:33.840
It could.

01:30:34.960 --> 01:30:37.340
And I, uh, think that's possible.

01:30:38.420 --> 01:30:45.100
Uh, but it's, it's, it marks a sign.

01:30:45.100 --> 01:30:51.660
She said to where the, the, the darkness would be exposed and the truth would be revealed.

01:30:53.020 --> 01:30:59.900
So I think we're going to learn something over the next couple of years that, you know, and this was 12 years ago.

01:30:59.900 --> 01:31:01.920
I said this 13 years ago, 2012.

01:31:02.320 --> 01:31:02.620
Yeah.

01:31:02.800 --> 01:31:03.120
Right.

01:31:03.620 --> 01:31:10.640
And how, when these missiles started flying and the orbs started appearing, that got a lot of attention on me real quick.

01:31:11.020 --> 01:31:11.400
Yeah.

01:31:11.620 --> 01:31:12.320
I'm, it's funny.

01:31:12.320 --> 01:31:14.100
I'm caught between two minds.

01:31:14.280 --> 01:31:21.780
One is, you know, I think even the book of Matthew, it's something like nobody knows the apocalypse other than God.

01:31:21.980 --> 01:31:22.100
Right.

01:31:22.540 --> 01:31:24.960
Uh, paraphrasing, but yeah, nobody knows the day.

01:31:25.460 --> 01:31:32.060
Um, and then on the other hand, it does feel like just this gestalt sense of like things are getting weirder.

01:31:32.240 --> 01:31:32.480
Yeah.

01:31:33.060 --> 01:31:35.800
Dark truths are being revealed ongoing.

01:31:36.080 --> 01:31:36.300
Yeah.

01:31:36.300 --> 01:31:37.500
It feels like it's already started.

01:31:38.200 --> 01:31:42.440
Um, and it feels like we're on the verge of, uh, uh, some sort of paradigm shift.

01:31:42.500 --> 01:31:43.800
Yeah, we are definitely.

01:31:44.220 --> 01:31:44.560
Yeah.

01:31:45.100 --> 01:31:45.500
Yeah.

01:31:45.720 --> 01:31:46.920
I agree with that a hundred.

01:31:47.020 --> 01:32:02.120
And I, I think everybody sees something coming and a new knowledge just coming and a new shift that, um, things that I know that, um, imagine a world without oil.

01:32:03.020 --> 01:32:03.280
Mm.

01:32:04.060 --> 01:32:08.420
So you think we're going to have free energy at some point soon or something?

01:32:08.500 --> 01:32:10.420
Imagine the world without rockets.

01:32:11.080 --> 01:32:11.460
Right.

01:32:11.460 --> 01:32:15.220
So that kind of knowledge alone would change everything.

01:32:15.420 --> 01:32:15.740
Right.

01:32:16.160 --> 01:32:17.220
All of humanity.

01:32:17.600 --> 01:32:19.060
And so that's in our future.

01:32:19.360 --> 01:32:36.500
Well, that was Thomas Townsend Brown's vision, you know, a world beyond rockets that, you know, he had this model of electrogravitics, which connected electromagnetism and gravity, which, you know, in kind of our standard physics is, you know, we don't have a link between those two things.

01:32:36.580 --> 01:32:36.880
Right.

01:32:36.880 --> 01:32:36.940
Yeah.

01:32:36.940 --> 01:32:49.500
And, uh, if you were to get a link, if the input was pure electromagnetism or, you know, electrical and the output was some sort of gravity gravitational perturbation, um, that, that, that would be paradigm shift.

01:32:49.680 --> 01:32:49.880
Exactly.

01:32:49.880 --> 01:32:54.060
I mean, you'd get well beyond what SpaceX is, which is extremely inefficient.

01:32:54.360 --> 01:33:04.460
You know, most of, I believe the, the Starship, their latest rocket is, I think it's 5,000 metric tons and a, an extremely high percentage of that.

01:33:04.520 --> 01:33:07.300
I mean, the payload capacity of it is like 150 tons.

01:33:07.600 --> 01:33:10.280
So that ratio alone, it's all fuel.

01:33:10.420 --> 01:33:11.640
The whole thing is fuel.

01:33:11.780 --> 01:33:12.020
Right.

01:33:12.160 --> 01:33:12.960
That's not efficient.

01:33:13.080 --> 01:33:16.260
That's not alien interstellar space travel.

01:33:16.360 --> 01:33:17.040
It doesn't make sense.

01:33:17.040 --> 01:33:20.080
Well, I imagine a day that we won't need those things.

01:33:20.540 --> 01:33:20.740
Hmm.

01:33:21.400 --> 01:33:23.600
In fact, they probably already had that.

01:33:23.840 --> 01:33:24.560
Do you think they did?

01:33:24.740 --> 01:33:25.620
I think so.

01:33:25.920 --> 01:33:26.240
Really?

01:33:26.660 --> 01:33:27.680
I think it's possible.

01:33:28.260 --> 01:33:29.120
So why not?

01:33:29.200 --> 01:33:31.060
Cause why not let it out then?

01:33:31.820 --> 01:33:35.720
Because it, it would change everything.

01:33:36.100 --> 01:33:36.380
Hmm.

01:33:36.420 --> 01:33:41.000
It could, it could create, it's something that has to be given slowly.

01:33:41.540 --> 01:33:42.500
It's too disruptive.

01:33:42.880 --> 01:33:43.580
Too disruptive.

01:33:43.780 --> 01:33:44.000
Yeah.

01:33:44.000 --> 01:33:46.940
It would definitely be destabilizing for institutions.

01:33:47.700 --> 01:33:53.080
You know, if you had, say right now we're paying, I'm just going to throw fake numbers

01:33:53.080 --> 01:33:59.600
out there, but $15, you know, per kilowatt hour for electricity or whatever, if that reduced

01:33:59.600 --> 01:34:06.100
to 10 cents per kilowatt hour, a whole lot of institutions would kind of crumble.

01:34:06.580 --> 01:34:10.800
Corporations would experience a lot of like for the people who are like there, it wouldn't,

01:34:10.800 --> 01:34:12.520
you know, destabilize things.

01:34:12.520 --> 01:34:13.360
I think that's crazy.

01:34:13.420 --> 01:34:14.020
I think it would.

01:34:14.020 --> 01:34:15.480
I think it would be very positive.

01:34:16.040 --> 01:34:21.160
Well, it would be in the end, but imagine the oil tankers, the thousands of them are

01:34:21.160 --> 01:34:24.400
refineries and all the jobs that's involved with it.

01:34:24.680 --> 01:34:24.900
Sure.

01:34:25.560 --> 01:34:25.780
Yeah.

01:34:25.780 --> 01:34:28.160
But then imagine the abundance on the other side.

01:34:28.280 --> 01:34:28.520
Yeah.

01:34:28.640 --> 01:34:33.060
All of those people, their quality of life would be dramatically better.

01:34:33.060 --> 01:34:33.180
Different.

01:34:33.180 --> 01:34:33.820
Better.

01:34:34.040 --> 01:34:34.300
Yeah.

01:34:35.600 --> 01:34:37.460
So is that the new knowledge?

01:34:37.540 --> 01:34:38.080
I don't know.

01:34:38.460 --> 01:34:45.840
But I think that there's a whole lot of things that are going to come forward that have been

01:34:45.840 --> 01:34:46.700
hidden from us.

01:34:46.960 --> 01:34:51.200
And the main thing is the truth that we're not alone.

01:34:51.660 --> 01:34:51.900
Yeah.

01:34:52.580 --> 01:34:54.300
I mean, well, that's clear to me.

01:34:54.740 --> 01:34:57.760
You know, I think that's definitely a thing.

01:34:57.760 --> 01:35:02.620
And so I believe next year we'll be closer to that than ever.

01:35:02.960 --> 01:35:03.220
Yeah.

01:35:03.360 --> 01:35:06.240
And the word apocalypse, by the way, you know what that means?

01:35:06.640 --> 01:35:06.860
Yeah.

01:35:07.460 --> 01:35:07.860
Unveiling.

01:35:08.160 --> 01:35:08.380
Yeah.

01:35:08.480 --> 01:35:09.740
To reveal a secret.

01:35:09.820 --> 01:35:10.740
To reveal a secret.

01:35:11.000 --> 01:35:11.260
Yeah.

01:35:11.360 --> 01:35:11.560
Yeah.

01:35:11.940 --> 01:35:12.360
That's all.

01:35:12.480 --> 01:35:16.880
And people think when you hear that, and if you look on Google, it says the ultimate destruction,

01:35:17.060 --> 01:35:17.580
the end.

01:35:18.220 --> 01:35:19.660
You know, it's lying to us.

01:35:19.700 --> 01:35:21.240
That's not what the word means at all.

01:35:21.440 --> 01:35:21.580
Yeah.

01:35:21.580 --> 01:35:24.940
It means to reveal that which has been hidden.

01:35:24.940 --> 01:35:27.880
And it's the veil thinning.

01:35:28.160 --> 01:35:31.400
And I think for some people that will be very good and for other people it will be very

01:35:31.400 --> 01:35:31.640
bad.

01:35:31.760 --> 01:35:33.580
It depends on your orientation to it.

01:35:34.060 --> 01:35:40.140
And I think it does have this connotation of, you know, Beezlebub coming down and breathing

01:35:40.140 --> 01:35:41.560
fire onto everybody.

01:35:41.780 --> 01:35:43.040
It's sorting people and whatever.

01:35:43.160 --> 01:35:50.660
But like, I think if you were oriented in a good way spiritually, you know, I don't think

01:35:50.660 --> 01:35:52.380
it'll necessarily be bad for you.

01:35:52.380 --> 01:35:57.720
I also don't even, you know, we're talking about it like it's one, you know, crazy event

01:35:57.720 --> 01:35:59.300
with these like divine beings.

01:35:59.620 --> 01:36:01.100
Maybe it's like a slow moving thing.

01:36:01.100 --> 01:36:02.780
That's exactly the way I see it.

01:36:02.800 --> 01:36:04.920
It's not like snap your fingers and something.

01:36:05.180 --> 01:36:08.640
We're not going to wake up on Easter or whenever that time happens.

01:36:08.820 --> 01:36:09.120
Yeah.

01:36:09.120 --> 01:36:17.540
I'm torn, by the way, because for eight years I wrote and talked about this alignment being

01:36:17.540 --> 01:36:24.320
in September or somewhere in the fall, because that was the date given to me by some people

01:36:24.320 --> 01:36:25.180
into astrology.

01:36:25.460 --> 01:36:29.240
And then they come back right when I go to write my book and say, oh, we made a mistake.

01:36:29.280 --> 01:36:29.900
It said Easter.

01:36:29.900 --> 01:36:35.180
And I thought, well, that sounds plausible because the lady's always coming around Easter.

01:36:35.180 --> 01:36:39.380
I have this insane experiences every year at Easter.

01:36:39.760 --> 01:36:41.200
Are you still having them?

01:36:41.440 --> 01:36:41.780
Yeah.

01:36:42.020 --> 01:36:42.800
That's amazing.

01:36:43.140 --> 01:36:44.520
So you still speak to this?

01:36:44.540 --> 01:36:44.900
Every year.

01:36:45.240 --> 01:36:50.580
And you think it's the Virgin Mary, Hathor, Demeter, you think all of these?

01:36:50.580 --> 01:36:55.020
I think it's the Sophia, the wisdom, the Holy Spirit.

01:36:55.120 --> 01:36:57.460
So that would be kind of the Gnostic version or something.

01:36:57.840 --> 01:36:58.180
Yeah.

01:36:58.300 --> 01:36:58.500
Yeah.

01:36:58.620 --> 01:37:03.260
That's who I think that this being is.

01:37:03.300 --> 01:37:07.240
It was a spirit, and it was definitely holy in her presence, right?

01:37:07.480 --> 01:37:15.260
And so, and she physically impacted me because the wind blew me backwards to the ground.

01:37:15.260 --> 01:37:20.360
It was such a blast of wind that blew me down, and I started researching that.

01:37:20.580 --> 01:37:26.980
And the word spirit is the wind, right?

01:37:27.100 --> 01:37:29.800
And the word Holy Spirit is the breath of God.

01:37:30.260 --> 01:37:34.260
But it was the wind that affected me, and the power from it.

01:37:35.080 --> 01:37:38.560
This cowl came over me, but the wind pushed me back.

01:37:39.180 --> 01:37:40.120
What does she look like?

01:37:40.460 --> 01:37:46.280
Looked like the most beautiful 35, 40-year-old woman you've ever seen.

01:37:46.280 --> 01:37:52.480
It's just glowing, and typical Virgin Mary apparition type thing.

01:37:52.940 --> 01:37:57.820
And, you know, this thing, this spirit appears in every country.

01:37:58.100 --> 01:38:02.420
It appeared to the Native Americans in the Wild West back.

01:38:02.540 --> 01:38:04.820
You know, they called her the white buffalo calf lady.

01:38:04.820 --> 01:38:14.940
The Egyptians called her Hathor, and earlier before Met, and the birth mother, the creator.

01:38:15.400 --> 01:38:19.760
In Proverbs, in the Bible, chapter 8 and 9 talks about wisdom.

01:38:20.580 --> 01:38:27.140
It's the name of the chapters, and it talks about, and she was created before the earth was created,

01:38:27.260 --> 01:38:28.680
before the beginning of time.

01:38:29.340 --> 01:38:29.780
Wow.

01:38:30.220 --> 01:38:31.120
So, who is she?

01:38:31.180 --> 01:38:31.700
I don't know.

01:38:32.360 --> 01:38:34.220
But that's my thought.

01:38:34.660 --> 01:38:39.680
What was the feeling that came over you when you saw her, when you see her regularly?

01:38:40.800 --> 01:38:48.600
It's, when I first saw her, it was very impactful because the cow ran me over,

01:38:48.740 --> 01:38:51.520
and so I had this extreme fright to start with.

01:38:51.520 --> 01:38:57.180
And then I land on my back, and I roll over to get up and run, and there's this beautiful woman.

01:38:57.360 --> 01:39:01.060
So, I went from extreme fear to, oh, my God, what is this in front of me?

01:39:01.160 --> 01:39:03.900
Is the cow running you over part of the whole thing?

01:39:04.040 --> 01:39:06.600
That was part of her coming at me.

01:39:06.700 --> 01:39:11.740
She came at me at night out of the darkness as a wind.

01:39:11.860 --> 01:39:15.440
The wind hit me, and as I'm going backwards to the ground,

01:39:15.440 --> 01:39:20.900
and I see a translucent cow run over the top of me, and I could see stars up through the thing.

01:39:21.480 --> 01:39:22.400
I'm like, oh, my God.

01:39:22.500 --> 01:39:24.400
And I was frightened so bad.

01:39:24.480 --> 01:39:26.840
I landed on my back, and I turned to get up and run,

01:39:26.900 --> 01:39:31.860
and there's this woman about from here to that camera, three feet off the ground, hovering.

01:39:32.020 --> 01:39:34.500
And she looked at me, and she said, you know why I'm here.

01:39:34.500 --> 01:39:42.500
And I'll tell you why she said that, because five years had gone by, 2007 to 2012.

01:39:43.720 --> 01:39:49.000
And I had been beaten down and broken by the community.

01:39:49.780 --> 01:39:51.580
My children were falling apart.

01:39:52.480 --> 01:39:55.440
The schools and the teachers were calling them to the side,

01:39:55.540 --> 01:39:56.700
is your dad crazy?

01:39:56.900 --> 01:39:58.040
We hear about all this.

01:39:58.080 --> 01:39:59.020
Are you all right?

01:39:59.020 --> 01:40:02.540
Somebody from there called social services on me,

01:40:02.640 --> 01:40:05.060
and I had to fight to be at home with my children.

01:40:05.160 --> 01:40:06.060
It was that bad.

01:40:06.200 --> 01:40:12.960
So five years of that, I walked out on Easter, Saturday night, Easter of 2012.

01:40:13.600 --> 01:40:14.840
Sunday morning is Easter, right?

01:40:15.000 --> 01:40:20.520
And I shouted to this guy, thank you for saving me.

01:40:20.680 --> 01:40:22.040
Thank you for healing me.

01:40:22.840 --> 01:40:24.300
But you've ruined my life.

01:40:24.300 --> 01:40:29.700
Now my children are affected, and I have caused them great harm.

01:40:30.140 --> 01:40:34.640
And I'll never speak about this again, even though I had the desire.

01:40:35.160 --> 01:40:39.560
They put this in me, like the famous movie, Close Encounters,

01:40:39.620 --> 01:40:43.920
where you see he's making a mashed potato mountain in dirt,

01:40:44.040 --> 01:40:45.780
and he's throwing it in the window in bushes,

01:40:45.980 --> 01:40:47.860
and he's creating Devil's Sour, right?

01:40:47.940 --> 01:40:49.980
He didn't know what it was, but it was in his head.

01:40:50.600 --> 01:40:51.640
So I was that guy.

01:40:51.640 --> 01:40:53.060
I had to tell everybody.

01:40:54.300 --> 01:40:57.640
And the more I told it, the more trouble I got myself into.

01:40:58.580 --> 01:41:03.120
And what you're referencing with your family is Junior, your son,

01:41:03.200 --> 01:41:08.740
who had gone looking for you, also saw beings, was really shocked

01:41:08.740 --> 01:41:10.800
at what he experienced.

01:41:11.460 --> 01:41:15.480
It was a community that caused him to want to leave home.

01:41:15.580 --> 01:41:15.880
Really?

01:41:16.080 --> 01:41:16.400
Yeah.

01:41:17.240 --> 01:41:17.560
Yeah.

01:41:17.900 --> 01:41:21.940
He's 17 years old, and my right hand was with me everywhere I went.

01:41:21.940 --> 01:41:28.060
And we come home telling the world about it, and now the whole community has come on us.

01:41:28.320 --> 01:41:33.420
And so five years into it, I'm out telling the heavens, I quit.

01:41:33.540 --> 01:41:35.240
I'll never talk about it again.

01:41:35.420 --> 01:41:38.160
And then she appears and says, you know why I'm here.

01:41:39.160 --> 01:41:41.420
This is your burden you must bear.

01:41:41.660 --> 01:41:43.000
You have to tell what you know.

01:41:43.000 --> 01:41:50.660
And if you do, I will allow you to video record and film my presence and share it with others.

01:41:51.260 --> 01:41:52.000
The lady said that.

01:41:52.000 --> 01:41:53.100
She told me that.

01:41:53.180 --> 01:41:54.220
And are you going to?

01:41:54.380 --> 01:41:55.280
Well, let me tell you.

01:41:55.360 --> 01:41:59.100
From 2007 to 2012, I had zero data.

01:41:59.900 --> 01:42:05.000
I was out every night with a camera trying to get pictures to save myself from the community, right?

01:42:05.000 --> 01:42:08.800
And the more I tried, the less it would let me film it.

01:42:09.820 --> 01:42:12.820
It would be hovering in the trees behind my house.

01:42:13.180 --> 01:42:16.540
I'd pull the camera out, and it would vanish every time.

01:42:17.660 --> 01:42:19.640
So I was angry about that.

01:42:19.720 --> 01:42:21.760
I'm trying to prove myself sane.

01:42:22.140 --> 01:42:28.700
And my child is now left home because the community has just been tough.

01:42:28.700 --> 01:42:31.840
So she's like, you're not going to quit.

01:42:32.480 --> 01:42:33.620
I'm going to help you.

01:42:33.780 --> 01:42:38.040
So from that point forward, I started being able to film it and sharing it with anybody.

01:42:38.540 --> 01:42:52.040
And I've amassed terabytes and terabytes of data, video, photo, audio, and never a picture until 2012 when she came.

01:42:52.820 --> 01:42:56.240
Why do you think these guys from NASA are showing up at your door?

01:42:56.780 --> 01:42:58.180
We mentioned Tim Taylor earlier.

01:42:58.180 --> 01:42:59.720
He's a NASA mission controller.

01:42:59.980 --> 01:43:03.460
But Hal Pauvenmeyer also showed up originally.

01:43:04.460 --> 01:43:12.420
And I think you, Ryan, your son, mentioned that kind of at the end of his life, you realized that he was both CIA and NASA.

01:43:12.540 --> 01:43:13.200
Yeah, yeah.

01:43:13.480 --> 01:43:17.300
And so what do you think their interest in all of this is?

01:43:19.080 --> 01:43:20.860
And there are a lot more NASA guys.

01:43:21.140 --> 01:43:22.220
That was just two of them.

01:43:22.260 --> 01:43:22.500
Really?

01:43:22.500 --> 01:43:25.720
In fact, I had dinner with Hal's wife this weekend.

01:43:25.920 --> 01:43:27.580
She came from Florida.

01:43:28.180 --> 01:43:30.040
To Chris Jr.'s wedding.

01:43:30.280 --> 01:43:30.880
Oh, wow.

01:43:31.500 --> 01:43:32.520
Yeah, we loved them.

01:43:33.160 --> 01:43:37.080
But there are a lot of other NASA guys that I'm currently talking with.

01:43:37.220 --> 01:43:37.460
Hmm.

01:43:38.240 --> 01:43:38.720
Several.

01:43:38.860 --> 01:43:41.960
One tells me wherever I go, but they're all interested.

01:43:42.320 --> 01:43:43.760
They tail you wherever you go?

01:43:43.900 --> 01:43:44.840
They're with me.

01:43:45.040 --> 01:43:45.340
Really?

01:43:45.520 --> 01:43:47.260
Yeah, usually traveling with me.

01:43:47.340 --> 01:43:48.960
Somebody associated with that.

01:43:49.060 --> 01:43:49.260
Yeah.

01:43:49.260 --> 01:43:51.080
What do you think they want?

01:43:51.600 --> 01:43:53.040
They all want to study it.

01:43:53.160 --> 01:43:54.040
They want to know.

01:43:54.220 --> 01:43:55.560
And they observe it with me.

01:43:55.800 --> 01:43:56.640
I take them out.

01:43:56.860 --> 01:43:58.700
You know, we do a lot of work.

01:43:58.900 --> 01:44:00.240
Are they with you in Austin, Texas?

01:44:00.840 --> 01:44:02.180
No, but they wanted to be.

01:44:03.040 --> 01:44:04.260
I only have one night.

01:44:04.500 --> 01:44:08.340
And my wife's friend traveled with me because she was at our house.

01:44:08.460 --> 01:44:10.400
And her kids are right down the street.

01:44:10.520 --> 01:44:10.860
Uh-huh.

01:44:11.460 --> 01:44:15.700
But usually I go nowhere without somebody with me.

01:44:15.920 --> 01:44:16.280
Hmm.

01:44:16.520 --> 01:44:17.220
For a reason.

01:44:17.540 --> 01:44:18.020
Wow.

01:44:18.380 --> 01:44:18.780
Yeah.

01:44:19.680 --> 01:44:26.080
I've had some things that caused me to want to have somebody with me all the time.

01:44:26.480 --> 01:44:31.980
What happened that caused you to want to not go anywhere unaccompanied?

01:44:33.920 --> 01:44:37.060
Well, I've been threatened a few times by different ones.

01:44:37.060 --> 01:44:40.940
And I was at the PSI Games this year.

01:44:41.140 --> 01:44:41.620
PSI Games.

01:44:41.720 --> 01:44:42.500
I call it PSI.

01:44:42.500 --> 01:44:43.120
PSI Games.

01:44:43.420 --> 01:44:46.040
And I came out of a conference speaking.

01:44:46.220 --> 01:44:50.720
And when I walked out the door, this mad lady comes running up to me and tries to kidnap me.

01:44:50.820 --> 01:44:51.140
What?

01:44:51.420 --> 01:44:51.820
Yeah.

01:44:52.520 --> 01:44:54.160
Has something with drugs on it.

01:44:54.360 --> 01:44:58.880
Tried to get me in a van with no tags on it.

01:44:58.960 --> 01:45:00.220
And security had to come.

01:45:00.300 --> 01:45:01.660
They had to call the law on her.

01:45:02.940 --> 01:45:03.460
Yeah, so.

01:45:03.600 --> 01:45:03.940
Crazy.

01:45:04.280 --> 01:45:05.060
Crazy people.

01:45:05.060 --> 01:45:09.700
Yeah, I imagine you attract a lot of nutty people.

01:45:09.940 --> 01:45:10.200
Big time.

01:45:11.200 --> 01:45:13.760
What do you think the Vatican knows about all of this?

01:45:13.800 --> 01:45:24.300
If they had a picture of you and they were doing some ceremony about you and you were supposed to come, what do you think they think of you?

01:45:24.780 --> 01:45:27.540
Well, I can share a couple of photos of you for that.

01:45:27.540 --> 01:45:37.940
But I got three pictures, several, quite a few paintings that they have in the Vatican that Diana sent me from there.

01:45:37.940 --> 01:45:54.520
And Pope Francis, she said to tell me that they know that they're angels, that they don't mean to harm us, but their energy, if they get excited, can cause harm to a human.

01:45:54.520 --> 01:45:59.880
So, just be careful and try to ask it not to get too close to you.

01:46:00.700 --> 01:46:06.240
And these three photos or paintings show orbs with angels in them.

01:46:07.640 --> 01:46:08.900
That's what they told me.

01:46:08.900 --> 01:46:17.740
Yeah, because, you know, you have St. Francis of Assisi, who she writes about in 13th century Mount Laverne in Italy.

01:46:18.040 --> 01:46:18.240
Right.

01:46:18.500 --> 01:46:22.240
Brother Leo is right next to him and he sees this angel.

01:46:22.240 --> 01:46:26.900
But if you look at the original Greek translation, it's a flaming torch.

01:46:27.120 --> 01:46:27.220
Yep.

01:46:27.380 --> 01:46:34.240
She thinks it's this UFO experience and that the stigmata he receives, these wounds on his hands are actually electromagnetic damage.

01:46:35.960 --> 01:46:44.560
That like, you know, Gary Nolan or somebody studying kind of modern experiencers interacting with UFOs might just say, oh, that's like an electromagnetic burn.

01:46:44.760 --> 01:46:46.760
Or you see it in Close Encounters of the Third Kind.

01:46:46.840 --> 01:46:48.500
You see the burn on his face.

01:46:48.500 --> 01:46:54.180
I got, yeah, I got radiation burns, plasma radiation.

01:46:54.380 --> 01:46:56.080
That's what NASA told me it was.

01:46:57.240 --> 01:47:00.620
So, you also got plasma radiation burns.

01:47:00.820 --> 01:47:01.460
No, I didn't.

01:47:01.540 --> 01:47:08.220
But I was warned a million times by Al Pobbenmeyer and different ones that NASA kept calling me honestly over and over.

01:47:08.480 --> 01:47:09.860
Don't let them get too close.

01:47:10.000 --> 01:47:10.240
Really?

01:47:10.240 --> 01:47:11.300
Don't get too close to them.

01:47:12.040 --> 01:47:17.880
Hal was telling me that they knew the voltage was like 33 million volts in one of these things.

01:47:17.880 --> 01:47:20.420
And if it got near me, it would kill me dead.

01:47:21.020 --> 01:47:26.580
So, they have like a scientific model of how these angels work at NASA.

01:47:27.100 --> 01:47:29.960
They know a lot more than we know than we think they do.

01:47:30.360 --> 01:47:31.880
They just don't share it, right?

01:47:32.020 --> 01:47:38.400
So, who is this like team like between CIA and NASA that knows a lot about angels?

01:47:39.040 --> 01:47:40.200
Well, I don't know that.

01:47:40.200 --> 01:47:44.440
But I know the NRO is the ones that have the keys to this thing.

01:47:44.660 --> 01:47:44.860
Really?

01:47:45.740 --> 01:47:46.780
And why do you think that?

01:47:47.060 --> 01:47:51.960
Because they have the keys to all the satellites and all the eyes on the sky.

01:47:52.260 --> 01:48:03.260
And they're the ones that every rocket, when it goes up, right, they observe every aspect of that rocket for reasons, for mechanical reasons.

01:48:03.260 --> 01:48:09.680
And for a surprise visit, that happens pretty much every time they launch one.

01:48:10.040 --> 01:48:12.040
Do you think that rockets attract UFOs?

01:48:12.440 --> 01:48:13.360
That's what I'm saying.

01:48:13.480 --> 01:48:15.800
Every time they send one up, it attracts them.

01:48:16.460 --> 01:48:20.240
And they'll come up and look at it if it has weapons on board.

01:48:20.760 --> 01:48:22.600
Does Tim Taylor know Elon Musk?

01:48:23.080 --> 01:48:23.500
Yeah.

01:48:24.060 --> 01:48:25.060
Do they work together?

01:48:25.480 --> 01:48:26.680
For sure, yeah.

01:48:26.980 --> 01:48:28.560
Did Tim ever tell you that?

01:48:28.560 --> 01:48:31.840
Well, he mentioned his name, but he didn't say it worked for him.

01:48:32.140 --> 01:48:33.960
But he controls all the launches.

01:48:34.780 --> 01:48:36.060
Controls all the launches?

01:48:36.100 --> 01:48:36.720
Tim does.

01:48:36.840 --> 01:48:38.160
He's the launch guy.

01:48:38.440 --> 01:48:39.980
He's the dragon.

01:48:40.140 --> 01:48:42.800
His console is called Dragon Control.

01:48:43.620 --> 01:48:46.700
And he controls all of the launches out of Cape Canaveral?

01:48:46.880 --> 01:48:47.460
He's the guy.

01:48:47.920 --> 01:48:48.580
He's the one.

01:48:49.120 --> 01:48:50.320
And I'll tell you what he does.

01:48:50.320 --> 01:49:08.040
When they fire a rocket up, right, they have these big ground-based cameras, like on a World War II battleship where they sit on a gun and they could turn a handle and the gun would go around and, you know, they could control this thing they're sitting on.

01:49:08.100 --> 01:49:11.480
Well, they have big binoculars like that.

01:49:11.600 --> 01:49:14.120
And they can get on this thing and follow this rocket up.

01:49:14.840 --> 01:49:17.680
And they got it to about 50,000 feet.

01:49:17.840 --> 01:49:18.780
Then it gets blurry.

01:49:18.780 --> 01:49:30.660
So at that point, it's intercepted by a WB-57 run out of Houston by a good friend of mine, which is National Reconnaissance Office, works with Taylor.

01:49:31.760 --> 01:49:35.700
So his crew's up there at 50,000 feet, and it intercepts the rocket.

01:49:36.240 --> 01:49:40.340
So they film it with seven cameras on that thing where it goes right on up.

01:49:40.340 --> 01:49:50.560
When it gets up to 100,000 feet, then it's intercepted by F-104 Starfighter, equipped with another seven or eight cameras on that.

01:49:50.760 --> 01:49:57.060
And so it trails it right on up until it runs out of sight of it, and then the satellites take it over.

01:49:57.060 --> 01:50:02.200
And the only ones that can look at the satellites are these NRO guys.

01:50:03.100 --> 01:50:08.320
And Tim walks out of his control into a private room where all the screens are.

01:50:09.160 --> 01:50:11.080
So his eyes are on all that.

01:50:12.620 --> 01:50:13.100
Fascinating.

01:50:13.260 --> 01:50:13.460
Yeah.

01:50:13.460 --> 01:50:16.680
How did he get into that line of work?

01:50:16.760 --> 01:50:21.660
Because if you read Launch Fever, I don't think he's traditionally credentialed or trained.

01:50:22.160 --> 01:50:25.940
Well, my friend from Houston told me he helped him get that position.

01:50:26.420 --> 01:50:27.680
And who's your friend from Houston?

01:50:27.680 --> 01:50:28.500
I can't say this.

01:50:28.500 --> 01:50:28.840
Okay.

01:50:29.200 --> 01:50:33.780
He lives right down the road from here on a big ranch right out here.

01:50:33.900 --> 01:50:34.780
Well, I'd love to meet him.

01:50:35.620 --> 01:50:36.020
Yeah.

01:50:36.820 --> 01:50:38.180
We can figure it out.

01:50:38.180 --> 01:50:39.740
I'll show you a picture of him later.

01:50:39.820 --> 01:50:40.560
Okay, cool.

01:50:42.320 --> 01:50:42.800
Wow.

01:50:43.200 --> 01:50:43.680
Fascinating.

01:50:44.080 --> 01:50:48.180
And because Tim also works at Aerospace Corporation, right?

01:50:48.300 --> 01:50:48.480
Yeah.

01:50:48.820 --> 01:50:51.880
And what do you think the link is between NASA and Aerospace Corporation?

01:50:52.760 --> 01:50:55.000
I know a lot of those guys are NRO.

01:50:55.320 --> 01:50:55.660
Okay.

01:50:56.200 --> 01:50:56.600
Interesting.

01:50:56.980 --> 01:50:59.260
And they carry BlackBerrys everywhere they go.

01:51:00.020 --> 01:51:00.540
BlackBerrys?

01:51:00.720 --> 01:51:01.000
Yeah.

01:51:01.160 --> 01:51:03.320
Not iPhones, Androids.

01:51:03.340 --> 01:51:05.520
They have all that, but they have BlackBerrys.

01:51:05.520 --> 01:51:06.340
They do their business.

01:51:06.500 --> 01:51:06.800
Mm.

01:51:07.580 --> 01:51:09.340
Do you think he's a time traveler?

01:51:10.180 --> 01:51:11.740
I think it's entirely possible.

01:51:13.040 --> 01:51:17.720
You know, honestly, I can tell you a story about him.

01:51:17.860 --> 01:51:18.140
Yeah.

01:51:19.080 --> 01:51:20.120
It's in my book.

01:51:20.460 --> 01:51:20.660
Yeah.

01:51:20.820 --> 01:51:22.280
I think it made it in.

01:51:22.420 --> 01:51:30.660
I wrote 140,000 words, and we only published 85, and that was what they recommended for the right size of the book, right?

01:51:31.580 --> 01:51:34.060
But in one of the stories, I talk about Tim.

01:51:35.520 --> 01:51:46.500
And right after we came back from Zanesville, Ohio, he came to my house, and we had this famous tree on my yard that caught fire.

01:51:46.500 --> 01:51:48.600
There's a video out on the Internet.

01:51:48.740 --> 01:51:50.720
You can see Chris Bledsoe burning tree.

01:51:50.880 --> 01:51:55.560
Well, we had this tree that just spontaneously combusted in the backyard.

01:51:56.080 --> 01:51:57.540
It rained for two days.

01:51:57.660 --> 01:51:58.460
The ground's wet.

01:51:58.660 --> 01:51:59.440
Everything's wet.

01:51:59.440 --> 01:52:09.000
And my wife and I walk out the back door at 9 o'clock, and this poof, it erupted into flames and was shooting 20, 15 feet up through the tree.

01:52:09.000 --> 01:52:16.040
And she put it out three times with a hosepipe and kept re-igniting itself.

01:52:16.540 --> 01:52:22.380
And so that got the attention of everybody, and Tim wanted to see this tree, so he's at my house.

01:52:22.700 --> 01:52:24.200
I picked him up at the airport.

01:52:25.540 --> 01:52:28.760
He goes to my daughter's homecoming game that night.

01:52:29.140 --> 01:52:32.320
She was a little homecoming princess in the 10th grade.

01:52:32.320 --> 01:52:38.220
Now she has a double master's from NYU, so that's been a long time ago, right?

01:52:40.100 --> 01:52:51.740
We walk up to this tree and having just a good conversation, and all of a sudden, the one side of the tree is open where it burnt from the inside.

01:52:51.920 --> 01:52:55.360
The tree caught fire in the inside and burnt a hole through the side of the tree.

01:52:55.360 --> 01:53:06.580
And when we walked up to it, he walks up and puts his head right up to look up in the tree, and all of a sudden, this snake comes out of the tree, this silver snake.

01:53:06.680 --> 01:53:10.140
And it was perfectly—I'd never seen anything like it ever.

01:53:10.220 --> 01:53:12.400
It was silver as a silver automobile.

01:53:12.760 --> 01:53:13.900
It was a perfect color.

01:53:15.320 --> 01:53:17.560
He jumps back, and he grasps for air.

01:53:17.620 --> 01:53:18.980
Oh, my God, just like that.

01:53:18.980 --> 01:53:37.280
And he looks at me, and he was short with words, and he said, you know, my grandmother is full-blooded Choctaw Indian, and I went to school on a minority grant.

01:53:38.680 --> 01:53:46.580
My grandma told me if I ever saw a silver snake—it was part of their history, right?

01:53:46.580 --> 01:53:48.900
She said it would be a message from God.

01:53:50.180 --> 01:53:57.000
And he saw that and told me all about it, but I watched his reaction, and it got the best of him when that snake came out of that tree.

01:53:57.080 --> 01:53:58.500
And you saw the snake?

01:53:58.600 --> 01:53:59.980
I was standing beside him, yeah.

01:53:59.980 --> 01:54:02.840
What do you think the message could have been from God?

01:54:02.840 --> 01:54:09.880
It was a message for him to understand this whole thing was from God somehow or another.

01:54:09.880 --> 01:54:23.620
And how does—one of the most interesting things I wonder is, if you read American Cosmic or talk to Diana Pasolka, it's almost like they visited the Vatican archives.

01:54:24.320 --> 01:54:33.040
He figured out a way in before she had gotten there, and then they were sort of celebrating him at the Vatican Observatory.

01:54:33.040 --> 01:54:39.680
Like, why would the Vatican Observatory know who a random NASA mission controller is?

01:54:39.680 --> 01:54:42.260
It makes me think he is not a random NASA mission controller.

01:54:42.260 --> 01:54:44.460
Oh, he's not a random guy at all.

01:54:44.720 --> 01:54:48.700
He's, let's just say, he runs with the biggest.

01:54:49.680 --> 01:54:50.500
How so?

01:54:51.260 --> 01:54:52.680
Do you think he has a connection with the president?

01:54:53.100 --> 01:54:54.140
Yeah, absolutely.

01:54:54.560 --> 01:54:56.560
He briefed Obama on me.

01:54:56.660 --> 01:54:57.720
That's where this come from.

01:54:58.100 --> 01:54:59.400
He briefed Obama on you.

01:54:59.400 --> 01:55:04.080
It came from him with a dinner napkin from Camp David, Maryland.

01:55:04.600 --> 01:55:06.420
And you're sure of that?

01:55:06.420 --> 01:55:06.740
Positive.

01:55:07.980 --> 01:55:10.000
And did he tell you that he briefed Obama?

01:55:10.600 --> 01:55:13.380
No, he didn't tell me that, but I know that's what it means.

01:55:13.560 --> 01:55:17.240
Because of the letterhead.

01:55:17.320 --> 01:55:17.560
Yeah.

01:55:18.220 --> 01:55:19.420
And where it came from.

01:55:19.680 --> 01:55:24.840
Bob McGuire, who is, I think, former Intel and a friend of yours, came on the show, and he said,

01:55:24.940 --> 01:55:26.620
that cannot be faked.

01:55:26.720 --> 01:55:27.060
Right.

01:55:27.140 --> 01:55:28.660
That definitely came from Camp David.

01:55:28.800 --> 01:55:29.040
Yeah.

01:55:29.040 --> 01:55:35.140
It's a napkin and an envelope with a napkin partially obscuring the address that's on the

01:55:35.140 --> 01:55:35.500
envelope.

01:55:35.820 --> 01:55:39.580
I knew the address because it was the address of Chris Bledsoe.

01:55:40.240 --> 01:55:46.280
I knew the napkin because it was the presidential seal on a napkin from Camp David.

01:55:46.280 --> 01:55:54.740
There's only one way you can have that napkin because it's a crime to copy the presidential seal.

01:55:54.740 --> 01:55:59.240
There's only one person that can get you to Camp David.

01:55:59.240 --> 01:56:03.700
And the picture was mailed to him by Tim Taylor.

01:56:03.700 --> 01:56:05.700
By Tim Taylor.

01:56:05.700 --> 01:56:13.540
And the only person that story can have been told to in that envelope was Barack Obama.

01:56:13.540 --> 01:56:14.460
Oh, my God.

01:56:14.460 --> 01:56:16.400
Oh, my God.

01:56:17.000 --> 01:56:25.080
The letter to me is ironclad proof that Chris's story was taken all the way to Barack Obama.

01:56:25.080 --> 01:56:25.540
Yeah.

01:56:25.540 --> 01:56:26.880
Via Tim Taylor.

01:56:27.020 --> 01:56:27.300
Yes.

01:56:28.000 --> 01:56:31.440
You might think he was trying to throw you off the trail if he said, I briefed the president

01:56:31.440 --> 01:56:32.680
and was bragging or whatever.

01:56:32.820 --> 01:56:34.540
But he didn't sound it out independently.

01:56:34.600 --> 01:56:34.840
Right.

01:56:34.900 --> 01:56:35.620
I found it out.

