02:55:44.640 --> 02:55:50.160
Like, like, you know, I'm sure I've explored all sorts of like crazy stuff, but, but in

02:55:50.160 --> 02:55:54.880
reality, I think it, you know, my, I think my worldview is actually sometimes crazier than

02:55:54.880 --> 02:55:57.440
I can even communicate via the show.

02:55:57.480 --> 02:55:57.680
Yeah.

02:55:57.680 --> 02:56:03.000
And it's really about catching people up, you know, epistemically and like taking people

02:56:03.000 --> 02:56:05.920
through this like rigorous, like, well, let's start with the foundation.

02:56:05.920 --> 02:56:07.200
Like that photo is real.

02:56:07.200 --> 02:56:12.040
Well, it's been verified, you know, like you need to do that because we're in this materialist

02:56:12.040 --> 02:56:13.780
reductionist scientific paradigm.

02:56:14.020 --> 02:56:14.100
Right.

02:56:15.760 --> 02:56:20.880
But, and, and, and you'll make a lot of, you know, errors along the way, but yeah, it's

02:56:20.880 --> 02:56:25.640
this really kind of hard thing because you, you make one error and you get these kind of

02:56:25.640 --> 02:56:30.520
debunker skeptic types and they'll just hang on that one error for the whole.

02:56:30.600 --> 02:56:32.280
And it's like, they're seeing what they want to see.

02:56:32.280 --> 02:56:37.800
Well, the thing people give these debunkers and skeptics too much power.

02:56:38.060 --> 02:56:38.280
Yeah.

02:56:38.440 --> 02:56:39.000
Oh boy.

02:56:39.080 --> 02:56:40.600
I don't even pay them attention.

02:56:40.920 --> 02:56:41.140
Yeah.

02:56:41.380 --> 02:56:43.480
To me, they're just uninformed.

02:56:43.740 --> 02:56:49.240
Well, I think the thing that deflates them too is like, I'll admit, like I've gotten a

02:56:49.240 --> 02:56:50.700
whole ton of stuff wrong.

02:56:50.900 --> 02:56:53.160
Like, and I hope, I hope you would admit that too.

02:56:53.380 --> 02:56:53.400
Yeah.

02:56:53.400 --> 02:56:55.440
I have, I changed, you know, we learned.

02:56:55.640 --> 02:56:56.280
Yeah, that's right.

02:56:56.300 --> 02:56:56.520
Right.

02:56:56.660 --> 02:56:56.920
Yeah.

02:56:57.440 --> 02:56:57.660
Yeah.

02:56:57.700 --> 02:57:04.000
And as long as you can adapt with new information that comes in, you know, then this is all,

02:57:04.100 --> 02:57:05.960
it's, it's, it's really new territory.

02:57:06.260 --> 02:57:06.460
So.

02:57:06.560 --> 02:57:08.060
Oh, there's, there's no book.

02:57:08.820 --> 02:57:11.660
There's no, there's no vocabulary for this.

02:57:11.800 --> 02:57:12.120
None.

02:57:12.800 --> 02:57:19.460
It's all invisible and we have to create a vocabulary for it and we've got to put a story

02:57:19.460 --> 02:57:20.340
to it, right?

02:57:20.680 --> 02:57:22.020
As humans do that.

02:57:22.020 --> 02:57:29.560
And so you're constantly adjusting that as you go and pulling all the information together

02:57:29.560 --> 02:57:34.400
and down the road, you think, well, what you thought before is not correct, you know,

02:57:34.400 --> 02:57:35.760
so it could be different.

02:57:36.220 --> 02:57:38.580
So I leave an open mind to it.

02:57:39.020 --> 02:57:48.300
I try not to label it, but I will go so far as to say that it's been benevolent and I've

02:57:48.300 --> 02:57:55.260
seen healings from it and I know how it answers when I say certain words, it gets excited.

02:57:55.540 --> 02:57:56.200
Which words?

02:57:56.540 --> 02:57:57.080
The lady.

02:57:57.500 --> 02:57:57.860
Really?

02:57:58.200 --> 02:57:59.100
That's all you got to say.

02:57:59.200 --> 02:57:59.740
The lady.

02:57:59.960 --> 02:58:00.500
The lady.

02:58:00.680 --> 02:58:01.080
Interesting.

02:58:01.420 --> 02:58:01.600
Yep.

02:58:01.600 --> 02:58:07.120
When you start talking about her and I can do this, I could take a group of people outside

02:58:07.120 --> 02:58:08.260
at night.

02:58:08.400 --> 02:58:09.940
I've done it over and over and over.

02:58:10.060 --> 02:58:12.560
Take a mic if we've got a big enough group.

02:58:12.560 --> 02:58:20.680
It's gotten pretty simple because, and I shouldn't say it's simple, it's complex, but still it's

02:58:20.680 --> 02:58:25.140
happened so much that it's pretty crazy.

02:58:25.520 --> 02:58:30.560
Do you think there are pockets, air pockets of consensus reality?

02:58:30.560 --> 02:58:36.960
And what I mean by that is like, do you think, you know, the Mandela effect?

02:58:37.580 --> 02:58:42.060
So this idea that, you know, um, a lot of people in the nineties thought that Mandela

02:58:42.060 --> 02:58:48.460
died in prison, which he obviously didn't, you know, do you think that reality might work

02:58:48.460 --> 02:58:50.120
more like that than we think?

02:58:50.180 --> 02:58:56.780
And so certain mystical experiences happen and the people with eyes to see and ears to

02:58:56.780 --> 02:59:00.980
hear, experience it, and then other people walk away and they're like, yeah, I don't

02:59:00.980 --> 02:59:05.100
know, there's a thing that happened or whatever, or, you know, or they like will superimpose

02:59:05.100 --> 02:59:07.720
some prosaic explanation upon the thing.

02:59:07.900 --> 02:59:14.120
And reality itself is far more fractured, malleable, and in the eye of the beholder than

02:59:14.120 --> 02:59:15.060
what it is.

02:59:15.060 --> 02:59:15.900
Yeah, and it's changing.

02:59:16.040 --> 02:59:17.420
It's constantly changing.

02:59:17.420 --> 02:59:19.800
Like the Mandela effect you talked about.

02:59:19.860 --> 02:59:25.400
One thing that surprised me is my wife and I've been married 43 years, right?

02:59:25.400 --> 02:59:28.740
So our honeymoon was in New York City.

02:59:28.860 --> 02:59:30.580
We'd never been there, either one of us.

02:59:31.740 --> 02:59:32.800
We had a plan.

02:59:32.880 --> 02:59:37.160
We wanted to see, see the train station, Grand Central Station, right?

02:59:37.280 --> 02:59:41.460
So we go to Grand Central Station and we get photos and videos and we took a helicopter

02:59:41.460 --> 02:59:44.960
ride and we did all kinds of things to experience New York.

02:59:46.140 --> 02:59:51.680
And so I'm looking at my old photos of Grand Central Station, right?

02:59:52.020 --> 02:59:53.140
Well, Google it now.

02:59:53.840 --> 02:59:54.860
It's not called that.

02:59:54.860 --> 02:59:58.380
It's called Grand Central Terminal and it says it's never been called that.

02:59:59.080 --> 03:00:03.400
But yet I got photos of Grand Central Station written on the thing.

03:00:03.400 --> 03:00:04.280
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

03:00:04.360 --> 03:00:07.360
But you see it now, it says Grand Central Terminal.

03:00:07.460 --> 03:00:08.240
What's that about?

03:00:09.040 --> 03:00:17.560
Well, you know, it's the Flintstones, the Berenstain Bears, all these things where people

03:00:17.560 --> 03:00:20.740
swear that, you know, it was like one way.

03:00:20.740 --> 03:00:24.500
And then you look at the record and it actually looks like there's another way.

03:00:25.120 --> 03:00:29.160
And, you know, it is this really amazing phenomena.

03:00:29.320 --> 03:00:30.840
And then you get into deeper studies.

03:00:30.840 --> 03:00:33.220
Like there's this neuroscientist, Wilder Penfield.

03:00:33.220 --> 03:00:40.700
And you realize that there is no way of distinguishing between false memories and true memories.

03:00:40.700 --> 03:00:45.120
And he shows this with the ability to implant false memories into mice and stuff.

03:00:45.120 --> 03:00:51.000
And then you get if there are these beings and any thoughts can be sort of implanted.

03:00:51.100 --> 03:00:56.460
You get into really weird ontological territory where the past and even Schrodinger himself

03:00:56.460 --> 03:00:59.040
would say a particle is measured in the present.

03:00:59.280 --> 03:01:01.340
You know, it might change its past.

03:01:01.340 --> 03:01:05.020
And you get into retrocausality in quantum mechanics.

03:01:05.220 --> 03:01:09.580
There's obviously spooky action at a distance, but there's also spooky action across time.

03:01:09.980 --> 03:01:18.940
It seems like if you have two entangled photons and two double slit experiments run with those, you know, entangled photons,

03:01:19.040 --> 03:01:22.320
it seems like photon B that you're doing the experiment with two days in the future.

03:01:22.320 --> 03:01:24.480
If you measure that and you don't measure the first one,

03:01:24.760 --> 03:01:29.260
the measurement of the one in the future is affecting the one of the measurement in the past.

03:01:29.260 --> 03:01:34.120
There's a great book called Biocentrism that this guy Robert Lanza writes about this stuff.

03:01:34.580 --> 03:01:41.540
So you get in a really trippy territory where the past becomes the present is this constricted present.

03:01:41.920 --> 03:01:46.240
And but it's like an hourglass where you have probable futures and probable pasts.

03:01:46.240 --> 03:01:46.440
Right.

03:01:46.440 --> 03:01:54.240
And the present is this measurement sensor that is single line of code updating the past and maybe updating the future at the same time.

03:01:54.980 --> 03:01:57.460
And it's this very strange sort of model.

03:01:57.460 --> 03:02:02.780
But you there's no real way to argue against that other than physical artifacts.

03:02:02.940 --> 03:02:09.320
So if you have physical artifacts around an event happening, you can argue, say, this is evidence that this happened this way or this happened another way.

03:02:09.820 --> 03:02:17.820
If you have conflicting physical artifacts where you don't have physical artifacts, it's it's totally one word against the other word.

03:02:17.880 --> 03:02:22.560
Or then you get into like numbers of people who believe one thing or numbers of people that believe another thing.

03:02:22.560 --> 03:02:25.600
But we have no idea how reality works.

03:02:25.840 --> 03:02:26.920
We have no idea.

03:02:27.160 --> 03:02:31.380
We have we have a very limited we are measurement sensors.

03:02:31.920 --> 03:02:36.440
And so, you know, this idea that science is some ontological statement of truth.

03:02:36.440 --> 03:02:38.120
Like, no, we're it's the map.

03:02:38.200 --> 03:02:39.180
It's not the territory.

03:02:39.940 --> 03:02:43.660
It's just, you know, we see like very limited scopes of reality.

03:02:43.880 --> 03:02:44.160
Right.

03:02:44.160 --> 03:02:46.040
And time is the weirdest thing of all.

03:02:46.560 --> 03:02:46.720
Yeah.

03:02:47.020 --> 03:02:51.500
That that has messed with me ever since I went there and saw that.

03:02:51.640 --> 03:02:55.160
And now everything I dig up, it says it was never called that.

03:02:55.400 --> 03:02:55.620
Yeah.

03:02:55.740 --> 03:02:56.220
Grand Central.

03:02:56.340 --> 03:02:56.520
Yeah.

03:02:56.820 --> 03:02:58.100
But the sign was on the wall.

03:02:58.620 --> 03:02:59.100
Central Station.

03:02:59.200 --> 03:02:59.960
I was like, oh, of course.

03:03:00.060 --> 03:03:01.180
Grand Central Station.

03:03:01.440 --> 03:03:02.860
Go Google it now, though.

03:03:02.940 --> 03:03:03.820
It's not that.

03:03:03.860 --> 03:03:05.000
Grand Central Terminal.

03:03:05.120 --> 03:03:06.360
It doesn't even sound as good.

03:03:06.520 --> 03:03:06.780
Yeah.

03:03:06.840 --> 03:03:09.540
It's always been named that according to this.

03:03:09.720 --> 03:03:10.040
Yeah.

03:03:10.040 --> 03:03:18.000
So I don't know what that means, but it was really, it really opened my eyes to how weird

03:03:18.000 --> 03:03:20.000
this world we live in really is.

03:03:20.320 --> 03:03:27.480
How do you juggle, you know, a lot of these concepts might seem crazy to the average person.

03:03:27.480 --> 03:03:36.720
How do you juggle just facing, you know, relationships, issues, things in your own life versus these kind

03:03:36.720 --> 03:03:39.860
of deeper celestial metaphysical truths?

03:03:40.400 --> 03:03:43.880
Those two things seem kind of hard to juggle.

03:03:44.000 --> 03:03:48.160
I was talking to a friend yesterday and he has all these teachers, you know, kind of in

03:03:48.160 --> 03:03:49.060
the Eastern tradition.

03:03:49.280 --> 03:03:51.360
He's kind of his own mystic in a sense.

03:03:52.120 --> 03:03:53.680
And I think I can say this, actually.

03:03:53.700 --> 03:03:54.720
His name is Duncan Trussell.

03:03:54.880 --> 03:03:57.140
And he's, you know, I actually just met him.

03:03:57.200 --> 03:03:59.660
He's an amazing comedian, but I felt a kinship with him.

03:04:00.120 --> 03:04:07.940
And he said his teachers all said that, and these are like Eastern, you know, kind of

03:04:07.940 --> 03:04:13.200
Buddhists say that, you know, they know that the celestial realm exists, but they ignore

03:04:13.200 --> 03:04:15.800
it because what we need to do is here on earth.

03:04:15.920 --> 03:04:18.940
We have these kind of karmic path laid out in front of you.

03:04:18.940 --> 03:04:23.900
And so I'm sure a lot of people have this sort of escapist orientation towards this, this

03:04:23.900 --> 03:04:27.060
subject where they say, oh, well, take me up on the craft, you know.

03:04:27.400 --> 03:04:29.580
So how do you reconcile those two things?

03:04:29.580 --> 03:04:33.480
Because I don't.

03:04:33.680 --> 03:04:37.760
I mean, it's like, it's just, it's mind-bending, the whole thing.

03:04:37.900 --> 03:04:42.760
I'm still grappling with that, you know, to this very day.

03:04:43.220 --> 03:04:51.200
And I focus on, right now, my main focus is on the Rosetta Stone.

03:04:51.560 --> 03:04:51.940
Really?

03:04:52.920 --> 03:04:55.040
Why is your focus on the Rosetta Stone?

03:04:55.040 --> 03:05:00.560
Because I believe that I can find, I think I can get there.

03:05:00.780 --> 03:05:02.180
I think, I know it's talking.

03:05:02.660 --> 03:05:03.640
I know it is.

03:05:03.720 --> 03:05:10.500
I know it's talking multiple ways, not just telepathically, because that's hard to prove

03:05:10.500 --> 03:05:17.840
or explain, but I'm sure it's talking through frequency, through the light, pulses of light,

03:05:19.600 --> 03:05:24.240
with the right sensors and even some sort of Morse code or something.

03:05:25.040 --> 03:05:27.200
Multiple ways is trying to communicate.

03:05:27.540 --> 03:05:28.300
I've seen it.

03:05:28.400 --> 03:05:29.120
I know it.

03:05:29.220 --> 03:05:31.060
And I think one day we'll get there.

03:05:31.640 --> 03:05:34.600
You think the Rosetta Stone is trying to communicate with you?

03:05:34.820 --> 03:05:43.420
I think that Phenomenon is trying to talk to us and to find that Rosetta Stone, you know,

03:05:43.480 --> 03:05:46.220
that's just the language.

03:05:46.480 --> 03:05:48.120
I want to find the language of this.

03:05:48.260 --> 03:05:49.900
Of the beings.

03:05:49.900 --> 03:05:52.520
Yeah, and it's putting it out right now.

03:05:52.580 --> 03:05:53.060
It's talking.

03:05:53.520 --> 03:05:58.080
We just got to study it, and I'm working on a way to do that.

03:05:58.320 --> 03:06:01.080
Do you think their language is discoveries?

03:06:01.520 --> 03:06:03.040
Like, the discoveries we make?

03:06:04.040 --> 03:06:05.320
What do you think the language is?

03:06:05.360 --> 03:06:07.960
Do you think it's literal symbols and hieroglyphics?

03:06:08.000 --> 03:06:11.820
Because people say on the crafts that, you know, they see these sort of hieroglyphics.

03:06:11.940 --> 03:06:12.220
Yeah.

03:06:12.720 --> 03:06:15.440
I've heard biblical texts and all of them, too.

03:06:15.940 --> 03:06:18.960
And you think we'll be able to decode this?

03:06:19.320 --> 03:06:25.280
I think we can get actual real-time communication through the light and through sensors.

03:06:25.280 --> 03:06:27.500
If we can gather enough data.

03:06:28.420 --> 03:06:29.640
How would we do this?

03:06:29.740 --> 03:06:32.040
Put it in a quantum AI computer.

03:06:33.040 --> 03:06:37.980
And there's two of them that I could probably get access to.

03:06:38.100 --> 03:06:39.220
So you're working on this?

03:06:39.340 --> 03:06:40.420
I'm working on it, yeah.

03:06:40.500 --> 03:06:42.000
Have you decoded anything yet?

03:06:42.780 --> 03:06:44.500
Well, we're working on it.

03:06:44.500 --> 03:06:45.540
That's all I can say.

03:06:45.540 --> 03:06:47.060
Well, it sounds like you have decoded a little thing.

03:06:47.060 --> 03:06:48.580
Well, some, some, yeah.

03:06:48.760 --> 03:06:49.820
Anything you can give us.

03:06:50.960 --> 03:06:53.080
Enough to get me going full-time.

03:06:53.600 --> 03:06:57.700
I'm saying anything you can give us as far as hints as to what you've decoded.

03:06:57.700 --> 03:07:00.080
Well, I just said I know it's there.

03:07:00.940 --> 03:07:05.500
And I think we'll get there in the next four or five years, maybe.

03:07:05.720 --> 03:07:06.480
Maybe longer.

03:07:06.480 --> 03:07:13.580
Do you think there's something special about the pyramids that we'll learn soon or something?

03:07:13.900 --> 03:07:17.840
Because, I mean, one of your experiences was around the pyramids, obviously, Hathor.

03:07:18.160 --> 03:07:25.960
Well, I'm hearing that next year that something might be revealed from there.

03:07:25.960 --> 03:07:27.600
What will it be?

03:07:28.120 --> 03:07:32.640
Well, without getting ahead of what I was told this week, I've been invited to go down there

03:07:32.640 --> 03:07:40.800
and be involved in something that is going to release something that was hidden.

03:07:41.480 --> 03:07:42.040
Interesting.

03:07:42.520 --> 03:07:43.180
And what?

03:07:43.920 --> 03:07:45.320
Something under the pyramids?

03:07:45.740 --> 03:07:46.300
Possibly.

03:07:46.300 --> 03:07:48.780
Like a, like a little energy grid thing?

03:07:48.920 --> 03:07:50.200
I don't, they didn't tell me that.

03:07:50.380 --> 03:07:50.660
Okay.

03:07:50.740 --> 03:07:52.500
They just invited me to be a part.

03:07:52.720 --> 03:07:56.460
And the Egyptian antiquities authorities are part of it.

03:07:56.560 --> 03:07:56.840
Hmm.

03:07:57.480 --> 03:07:57.920
Fascinating.

03:07:58.120 --> 03:08:02.880
Well, I just interviewed the guy that did the synthetic aperture radar Doppler tomography scans

03:08:02.880 --> 03:08:06.840
of the structure under the Khafra chamber of the Giza pyramid.

03:08:07.280 --> 03:08:08.900
I can't say that's what it is.

03:08:08.900 --> 03:08:14.340
I can just say I got a call from the right people that wants me to be a part next year.

03:08:14.700 --> 03:08:15.380
Well, that's exciting.

03:08:15.600 --> 03:08:15.840
Yeah.

03:08:16.740 --> 03:08:17.460
Very interesting.

03:08:17.580 --> 03:08:20.820
So I think something's coming from there that's going to be real interesting.

03:08:21.140 --> 03:08:21.500
Wow.

03:08:22.080 --> 03:08:25.520
Like changing, thought changing.

03:08:25.900 --> 03:08:26.260
Wow.

03:08:26.660 --> 03:08:26.840
Yeah.

03:08:27.080 --> 03:08:28.940
Danny Jones, it was funny.

03:08:29.040 --> 03:08:32.980
Danny Jones, I think, came into the, your interview with him, maybe a little skeptical,

03:08:33.200 --> 03:08:36.480
but then he said he saw an orb with you outside of a diner or something.

03:08:36.480 --> 03:08:37.360
Well, he called me.

03:08:37.580 --> 03:08:38.900
He's like, I want you on my show.

03:08:39.040 --> 03:08:44.440
I'm like, Danny, I'd love to be on your show, but you got to do something for me.

03:08:44.440 --> 03:08:50.300
Um, I want to come a day or two early and I want to make you a believer, not a skeptic,

03:08:50.300 --> 03:08:53.760
because our interview will go differently if you're a believer.

03:08:53.760 --> 03:08:55.960
And he said, okay, okay.

03:08:55.960 --> 03:09:02.840
So we flew down and my daughter and I and my wife, and we had dinner there in Clearwater.

03:09:03.480 --> 03:09:08.520
Went over to Indian Rocks Beach, out on the beach, and he had his assistant with him with a camera.

03:09:08.520 --> 03:09:13.040
And I said, well, let's watch out of the ocean, because I can get it out.

03:09:13.300 --> 03:09:16.720
It appears up out of the ocean when I ask it.

03:09:16.760 --> 03:09:18.780
It's just like out of the sky, it comes up out of the sea.

03:09:19.760 --> 03:09:22.740
And suddenly here it came, two of them.

03:09:22.940 --> 03:09:23.300
Wow.

03:09:23.700 --> 03:09:24.680
And he filmed it.

03:09:24.720 --> 03:09:25.620
We all filmed it.

03:09:26.080 --> 03:09:27.100
Was he freaking out?

03:09:27.200 --> 03:09:27.460
Yeah.

03:09:28.100 --> 03:09:28.540
Wow.

03:09:28.920 --> 03:09:29.140
Yeah.

03:09:29.140 --> 03:09:35.440
Uh, we did that last week in, in California with some pretty amazing people.

03:09:35.560 --> 03:09:35.920
Wow.

03:09:36.400 --> 03:09:42.740
He also, Danny said he, I think he cut a small part of your interview where you talked about a neuralyzer,

03:09:42.980 --> 03:09:47.340
like some, like, machine that erased your memory after seeing something.

03:09:47.680 --> 03:09:49.260
Yeah, I had to not talk about that.

03:09:49.260 --> 03:09:50.460
You're not supposed to talk about that?

03:09:50.580 --> 03:09:50.740
Yeah.

